Definition: a formal religious ceremony conferring a specific grace on those who receive it
Example: the two Protestant ceremonies are baptism and the Lord's Supper; in the Roman Catholic Church and the Eastern Orthodox Church there are seven traditional rites accepted as instituted by Jesus: baptism and confirmation and Holy Eucharist and penance and holy orders and matrimony and extreme unction
Synonyms: adj, pert, sacramental, religious_ceremony, a, formal, religious, ceremony, conferring, specific, grace, on, those, who, receive, it, the, two, Protestant, ceremonies, are, baptism, and, Lord, s, Supper, in, Roman, Catholic, Church, Eastern, Orthodox, there, seven, traditional, rites, accepted, as, instituted, by, Jesus, confirmation, Holy, Eucharist, penance, holy, orders, matrimony, extreme, unction
Category: noun.act
